00:35:26.400 --> 00:35:28.560
Unfortunately, it never gets done.

00:35:30.890 --> 00:35:33.150
So what are some of the artists'
concerns with Enhanced Discs?

00:35:33.260 --> 00:35:38.790
Well, artists are really concerned about
the poor production by the label.

00:35:38.800 --> 00:35:43.100
There have been several instances where
we've actually had to recreate Enhanced

00:35:43.100 --> 00:35:47.680
CDs after the initial shipment because we
found the label found later or the artist

00:35:47.680 --> 00:35:52.030
found after the fact that the Enhanced
CD quite honestly didn't even function.

00:35:52.250 --> 00:35:57.100
And that's incredibly damaging because

00:35:57.390 --> 00:36:00.680
You damage your fan relations with
a poorly produced enhanced CD.

00:36:00.680 --> 00:36:02.780
This is your opportunity
to really communicate with

00:36:02.780 --> 00:36:04.080
your fans on a direct basis.

00:36:04.080 --> 00:36:08.880
And if you produce a damaged
ECD that's not at the par of the

00:36:08.880 --> 00:36:13.600
music on the enhanced disc or the
album packaging or everything else

00:36:13.670 --> 00:36:16.810
that everyone at the label and on
the artist side and the management

00:36:16.810 --> 00:36:19.690
company works so hard to produce,
then the consumers

00:36:19.690 --> 00:36:22.160
oftentimes feel screwed.

00:36:22.160 --> 00:36:24.190
What's on this enhanced disc?

00:36:24.280 --> 00:36:28.050
Why is there a sticker on this enhanced
CD package that says I have exclusive

00:36:28.110 --> 00:36:29.820
content when I can't even access it?

00:36:29.900 --> 00:36:33.660
And that also reduces perceived
value of the ECD compared to

00:36:33.660 --> 00:36:37.460
similar products in a very,
very crowded marketplace.

00:36:37.460 --> 00:36:41.560
So if you're on label X and you're
a rock band and label Y's rock

00:36:41.560 --> 00:36:46.570
band has a better enhanced disc and
obviously things are similar as far

00:36:46.570 --> 00:36:49.120
as radio play and everything else,
and there are all the other

00:36:49.120 --> 00:36:51.840
bazillion variables that go
into a typical artist campaign,

00:36:51.840 --> 00:36:55.870
then having a poor enhanced
disc is kind of like having

00:36:55.950 --> 00:36:57.990
a poor package or whatever.

00:36:58.150 --> 00:37:01.040
It's not a real,
it reduces the perceived value

00:37:01.060 --> 00:37:05.390
directly and it's all subconscious
but it actually has an impact.

00:37:06.900 --> 00:37:11.310
and of course potential inability to
grow the mailing list and all that other

00:37:11.310 --> 00:37:16.720
stuff that can be caused by rushed or
poor production on behalf of the label.

00:37:18.370 --> 00:37:22.980
Now I'm going to discuss briefly
how consumers view Enhanced CDs both

00:37:23.020 --> 00:37:26.810
currently and how they should.

00:37:27.800 --> 00:37:30.860
The current view of Enhanced
CDs by consumers is that they

00:37:31.000 --> 00:37:32.900
are very cheaply produced.

00:37:32.900 --> 00:37:36.650
The brand of ECD, you know,
every CD that you buy that's

00:37:36.650 --> 00:37:38.340
enhanced has that little ECD logo.

00:37:38.340 --> 00:37:44.560
At least in my opinion, has been very,
the value of that brand has been

00:37:44.720 --> 00:37:48.960
very sharply produced because
most of the ECDs that are produced

00:37:49.070 --> 00:37:50.970
are quite honestly terrible.

00:37:50.970 --> 00:37:52.970
And they meet very low standards.

00:37:52.990 --> 00:37:54.480
They lack any real content.

00:37:54.720 --> 00:37:57.820
And sometimes they don't even work.

00:37:57.820 --> 00:38:00.660
So they're of course of
limited value to the consumer.

00:38:00.730 --> 00:38:04.110
And therefore consumers at this point,
sometimes they don't even bother putting

00:38:04.110 --> 00:38:05.390
them in because there's no point.

00:38:05.570 --> 00:38:06.910
You know,
it's either not going to work or

00:38:06.910 --> 00:38:10.850
it's going to be the music video
that I've seen on MTV 5,000 times.

00:38:11.000 --> 00:38:12.300
So there's no point.

00:38:15.710 --> 00:38:20.790
How consumers should view ECDs is
obviously that they offer significant

00:38:20.790 --> 00:38:22.600
additional value without added cost.

00:38:22.630 --> 00:38:26.430
If you go to Best Buy and you
buy an album for $9.99 and it

00:38:26.430 --> 00:38:29.980
has an enhanced disc portion,
then there should be additional

00:38:30.020 --> 00:38:31.810
value on that enhanced disc.

00:38:33.300 --> 00:38:36.380
Access to exclusive collectible
content such as AIM icons that are

00:38:36.380 --> 00:38:39.200
specific for the Enhanced Disc,
desktop wallpaper,

00:38:39.260 --> 00:38:41.920
the screensaver technology kind
of stuff that I showed you,

00:38:41.920 --> 00:38:46.500
active desktops, desk sites,
all those sort of creative

00:38:46.500 --> 00:38:51.080
elements are very,
very exciting to a consumer.

00:38:51.080 --> 00:38:55.620
And many record labels that have
taken the time to produce high quality

00:38:55.620 --> 00:39:00.220
Enhanced Discs have actually seen
very positive results from those added

00:39:00.690 --> 00:39:03.150
value additions to the Enhanced Disc.

00:39:03.200 --> 00:39:05.650
The ability to communicate
with other fans,

00:39:05.650 --> 00:39:07.390
that's what fans really want.

00:39:07.470 --> 00:39:09.920
They want to find
like-minded souls online.

00:39:09.950 --> 00:39:13.450
And the ability to communicate
via direct links to the artist

00:39:13.450 --> 00:39:19.140
community or whatnot are incredibly
important for the consumer.

00:39:19.160 --> 00:39:22.530
And of course the ability to
stay up to date on how the,

00:39:22.610 --> 00:39:25.740
you know,
what's new in the world of the artist,

00:39:25.760 --> 00:39:28.230
you know,
latest news and tours and ticket

00:39:28.230 --> 00:39:30.600
sales and all that kind of cool stuff.

00:39:32.100 --> 00:39:33.920
So now what is the
future of Enhanced Discs?

00:39:33.960 --> 00:39:38.760
Well, the future is interesting.

00:39:38.790 --> 00:39:41.350
It really depends on how much
effort labels really want

00:39:41.350 --> 00:39:42.960
to put into Enhanced Discs.

00:39:43.080 --> 00:39:46.290
If the current trend continues,
then Enhanced Discs are

00:39:46.340 --> 00:39:50.620
going to fade away as a fad,
you know, part of the multimedia craze of

00:39:50.650 --> 00:39:53.920
producing CD-ROMs and they're really,
quite honestly,

00:39:53.920 --> 00:39:57.210
probably going to go away.

00:39:57.330 --> 00:39:58.950
But, you know,
it's really a great opportunity,

00:39:58.990 --> 00:40:01.550
as I said, for Enhanced Discs to be,
you know,

00:40:01.550 --> 00:40:05.330
