00:40:25.800 --> 00:40:30.040
So labels should really take the time
now to learn more about their consumers

00:40:30.040 --> 00:40:35.590
and involve them in ways that they really
won't be able to when the digital music

00:40:35.590 --> 00:40:37.220
revolution is really fully complete.

00:40:37.220 --> 00:40:40.100
We have things like Apple's
amazing new music store which

00:40:40.410 --> 00:40:42.100
enable consumers to buy music.

00:40:42.100 --> 00:40:46.320
And there's no enhanced portion
to buying a protected file.

00:40:46.320 --> 00:40:48.160
There's no,
it's just the audio straight and

00:40:48.230 --> 00:40:49.670
it's cheaper than buying a disc.

00:40:49.670 --> 00:40:52.520
So eventually you're going
to run out of time where,

00:40:52.610 --> 00:40:55.780
you know, eventually, you know,
obviously, you know,

00:40:55.780 --> 00:40:55.780
